Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.81,0:00:32.39,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I might lose my temper and accidentally shoot my comrades. Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:33.52,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.52,0:00:34.22,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell do you think you are!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.98,0:00:37.75,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive dodging.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.75,0:00:41.82,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I'd give you above 60 points for defense, but not quite 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.40,0:00:56.28,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He sliced the quartz in two!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.30,0:01:08.91,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell IS he?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.91,0:01:12.06,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I was opposed to releasing him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.84,0:01:16.09,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like everybody hates him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.09,0:01:18.99,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But I suppose he is pretty messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.23,0:01:21.91,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,He's my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:26.24,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Do NOT trust him, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.24,0:01:27.31,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:44.95,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:50.66,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,sign{3.16},0000,0000,0000,,Chapter Five
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,sign{3.16},0000,0000,0000,,Death's Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.80,0:04:11.16,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,So, Girghe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:15.07,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to hear your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:23.24,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I did step aside amidst the chaos, and once I regained myself, wandered about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.24,0:04:26.00,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,During which, found myself under enemy fire, and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:26.67,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,That is all. {the end?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.67,0:04:29.33,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I heard from Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:35.50,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You destroyed seven Golems, partially destroyed two officer's units, and nearly crippled another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:42.83,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,...Oh, right, I did that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.25,0:04:48.25,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe, you are hereby forbidden to carry a firearm or approach a Golem without my explicit approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:54.78,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Narvi, may Girghe be allowed to oversee the repairs to his Artemis?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.60,0:04:57.69,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me, Girghe!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.94,0:04:59.34,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:09.91,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.10,0:05:25.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Loggin, I have an important message.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:31.90,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Good to see you came back safely, Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.90,0:05:33.38,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.57,0:05:35.60,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:44.33,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure how to put it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:46.21,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He's really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.25,0:05:50.31,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just what did he do, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.65,0:06:05.09,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,About a year ago, I was on my way home from patrolling the border when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:09.08,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe had already been imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:14.61,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I went to his cell in hopes that I could learn why he did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.61,0:06:20.42,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,but he would only stare into space or sneer at me. He refused to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.85,0:06:29.45,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe was using one of ten Golems during a routine marching exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.46,0:06:34.87,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, he fired on a comrade, and used him as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:44.05,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,He then dispatched the remaining eight Golems without receiving so much as a scratch on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.19,0:06:50.91,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,After that, he turned himself in. {surrendered?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.84,0:06:55.26,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,That's the gist of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.64,0:07:00.10,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But is that what really happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:03.56,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he was the only one who lived, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:08.06,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,No. Only the first victim died.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.06,0:07:12.20,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,He avoided the remaining eight's vitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:19.00,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe never had any grudges or rivalries with those other men.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:22.97,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,There are several weapons before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.97,0:07:24.92,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Pick whichever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:29.61,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.21,0:07:35.57,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,What!? General True is dead!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.57,0:07:37.11,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,What about his remains?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.11,0:07:40.00,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy took possession of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.61,0:07:45.05,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, Nile...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.59,0:07:49.18,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,How do you intend to tell Captain Narvi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.18,0:07:50.28,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,The decision is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:07:57.14,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,She loved the man like a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:08:01.62,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Can you guarantee she won't become a hindrance to future operations upon hearing this? {wording?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:03.78,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid not, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.78,0:08:06.00,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Being a hindrance would be the least of our worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:14.16,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So we're left with two choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:16.69,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Either Loggin takes over as captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.69,0:08:20.33,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,or we keep her in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.98,0:08:33.13,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,We were soundly defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.39,0:08:36.00,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. It was a disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:38.03,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I even allowed Sir Iris to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:39.97,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:42.88,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make them pay...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.88,0:08:50.30,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Were it not for Colonel Io's assistance, \Nthe General would have been in grave danger. {omittied; “Troya”, Io's mech}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.57,0:08:54.59,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,I will slaughter every last Krishnan pig...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.70,0:09:01.43,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes my report on the Krisnan Artemis and the Black Golem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:03.80,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Leto, what's our current situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:04.69,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:09.87,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,Our right wing retreated along a separate route, but were annihilated by General Baldr's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.87,0:09:15.24,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,Of our forces that fought in the Arracan wastes, only 60% remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:19.07,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,However, we still managed to rendezvous with the main force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:23.26,Default,Let,0000,0000,0000,,Correct. Our force now numbers 120 strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.62,0:09:27.00,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,So in short, we may consider this skirmish a draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.59,0:09:30.67,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The Krisnans are not to be taken lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:35.23,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,A skirmish? We lost far too many men for a skirmish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.05,0:09:40.09,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,But the war has indeed just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.09,0:09:42.04,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,And what of the General?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:45.75,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,He's chosen to spend the night in the Hicherion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.71,0:09:53.20,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Iris...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.03,0:09:58.13,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't contain my excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.92,0:10:02.39,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Especially with those two enemy Golems running around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.05,0:10:35.15,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Rygart, we've received orders from the capital to withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:37.32,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Please begin preparations to move out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:38.52,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,We're withdrawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.53,0:10:39.78,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:43.57,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,If we remain here, it'll become difficult to maintain our supply line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:46.55,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we need to escort the wounded back to Binonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.55,0:10:47.63,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.43,0:10:49.46,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, by the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:50.21,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:55.22,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Could you stop calling me "Mr. Rygart"? It's kinda awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:57.63,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,What should I call you, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:11:00.68,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just call me Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.96,0:11:08.22,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Awkward?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.64,0:11:16.69,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe, we're pulling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.09,0:11:19.85,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You have permission to approach your Artemis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.46,0:11:26.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But you're not to board it until I give the order!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.13,0:11:29.44,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:31.48,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Very well! {is that a good "exit line"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.63,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Where's General Baldr?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:42.05,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.05,0:11:43.82,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse is on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.82,0:11:45.48,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,He's headed towards Pegusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.48,0:11:46.51,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Pegusa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.11,0:11:48.64,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.64,0:11:50.94,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We've confirmed that he's taking a detour there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.56,0:11:52.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:52.78,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.78,0:11:56.23,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second! There's a tiny village near Pegusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:59.86,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Have the residents been evacuated yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.74,0:12:06.09,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,If they don't make it in time, will Borcuse attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:08.51,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Why, is there something about that village?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.78,0:12:13.51,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,That village near Pegusa... is my hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.51,0:12:16.20,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,My little brother, Regarz, lives on the outskirts. {near/in?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.20,0:12:17.35,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.20,0:12:21.08,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Inform General Baldr at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.68,0:12:25.70,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart, I'm sure they'll inform the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.06,0:12:28.10,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, we need to get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:32.63,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart! Pack it in!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.18,0:12:34.02,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:37.31,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.17,0:12:48.35,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.15,0:12:55.23,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart deserted us to save his brother!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:57.00,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very sorry, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:12:58.80,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Send a squad after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.80,0:13:00.31,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Get me Kurozawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:13.96,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, Sigyn...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.78,0:13:17.09,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Could you continue your story from yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.23,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.23,0:13:24.50,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the one where Rygart climbed into a training Golem while playing hide and seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.50,0:13:29.41,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,and got thrashed around for an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:31.70,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.70,0:13:36.19,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,I was talking about the one where Rygart and \NHodr tried to sneak into the girl's dormitories,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:38.82,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,and Zess had to rescue them. {split/join these lines?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.74,0:13:43.75,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes. One day, out of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.75,0:13:47.01,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart boasted, "Tonight's the night!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.32,0:13:50.93,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,"For what?" I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:53.51,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,And he said, "I climb the mountain because it is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.51,0:13:56.85,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Men are born to create legends."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.92,0:13:59.19,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:00.77,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:05.54,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, security at the academy was quite strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:08.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,The girl's dorms in particular. No boys were allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.05,0:14:14.62,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,No less than eight female guards were stationed around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.76,0:14:23.71,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,There was also a rumor that a boy had been shot dead ages ago trying to sneak inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:27.13,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,They were so fired up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.45,0:14:31.25,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,So did Zess save them from being shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.25,0:14:33.55,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly, they invited him along...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.30,0:14:37.00,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous. I hope you get shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.95,0:14:40.44,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,So did they make it inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.44,0:14:43.25,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,That night, I heard shots from a Pressure Gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.29,0:14:47.49,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I looked out my window, and saw two silhouettes running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:50.69,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,They were chased off, like I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:55.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, Zess came to their rescue, and they got away safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.26,0:15:01.88,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,That's worlds apart from the Zess I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:09.80,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Zess was never one to show emotion to myself or others. He was very mature.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:14.31,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But whenever he was around Hodr and Rygart, he turned into a child again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:22.21,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Especially around Rygart. They fought all the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.32,0:15:30.99,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Sigyn?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.01,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.01,0:15:35.07,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Um, nothing. {shit, why'd they cut that line out?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:22.71,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Regarz!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.48,0:16:25.39,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Regarz!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.35,0:16:41.52,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Regarz...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:46.41,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:52.77,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,And here I thought I'd just swing by town...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.35,0:17:55.39,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.35,0:18:06.73,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Please step aside, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:11.82,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:14.15,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody is to move a muscle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:18.41,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who interferes will be executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.36,0:18:53.47,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What a peculiar stance. {lit; defense}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:22.59,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Those are some clever moves!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.35,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But you're wide open when you come down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.06,0:19:58.42,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to jointed \Nweapons, I have a bit of an edge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.42,0:19:58.88,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.62,0:20:29.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,How could the General...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.40,0:20:30.54,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.43,0:20:35.96,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? I'm wide open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.96,0:20:37.88,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to kill me, now's your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:42.70,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, why did you come to this backwater village alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:45.79,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Something tells me you aren't lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.79,0:20:49.14,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What went through your mind when you saw the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.73,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think, "That's just a part of war"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:59.19,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some reason you've come here alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.49,0:21:03.65,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But you were just too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:05.95,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.75,0:21:20.81,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to grab my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:47.46,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.74,0:21:50.06,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Where the hell is Bardess!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.90,0:22:04.42,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It was a smart move to let my Hicherion go airborne.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,{name check}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:12.39,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,If I had tried to stand my ground and guard, the frame would've given way from that hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.78,0:22:32.48,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,All I've got left is the Eastern Blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.27,0:22:37.62,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Now what? Are you going to fly off? {lit; jump}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:41.54,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't figure out why you came here by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.04,0:22:45.11,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But that makes this little detour worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.73,0:22:49.51,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Those maneuvers can't be done with quartz ligaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.19,0:22:53.38,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A relic from ages past, I suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.38,0:22:56.68,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,That might be just the thing Orlando needs! {implied: technology}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.55,0:22:59.41,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What a fortunate find! {wording?}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.31,0:23:59.83,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Charging right at your opponent... You bore me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.40,0:24:03.95,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You can't even close the gap between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.50,0:24:08.17,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone and ruined my good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.65,0:24:11.11,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Tie him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.26,0:24:16.73,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Chains won't cut it! I want five Golems holding him down too!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.73,0:24:20.12,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I want to transport it home with minimal damage. {rygart's golem}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.71,0:24:24.26,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Tear open the cockpit and drag the pilot out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.26,0:24:26.04,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Then kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.16,0:24:31.66,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, how many times have I told you not to charge into battle alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.66,0:24:37.20,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't accurately determine the Black Golem's combat prowess unless I fought him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.67,0:24:40.70,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But once I did, it became painfully clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.70,0:24:44.17,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the pilot that makes that Golem so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.17,0:24:47.94,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't the fighting style of a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.94,0:24:52.15,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,My interest is now held by that man in the Artemis.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.53,0:24:55.68,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we return to the camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.68,0:24:57.71,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, lets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.71,0:24:58.61,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.61,0:24:59.76,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.76,0:25:03.15,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Squads four and five, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.15,0:25:03.77,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.63,0:25:14.11,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, we'll take it from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.18,0:25:21.22,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We were too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.02,0:25:27.89,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,40 units headed southwest. But there's still about 20 left.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.45,0:25:30.15,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Plus about 200 infantry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.92,0:25:36.39,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a matter of time until they yank him out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.39,0:25:39.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Kurozawa, do you think we can attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.39,0:25:43.44,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of your mind!? Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.35,0:25:48.61,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,We've only got 4 Golems, 15 scouts and 5 engineers!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.61,0:25:51.94,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,If we charged in there, they'd tear us apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.29,0:25:55.80,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart's done for. We have to let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.80,0:25:58.01,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, let's get outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.01,0:26:01.62,Default,Kur,0000,0000,0000,,It pains me to say this, but I agree with Nile.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.15,0:26:06.22,Default,Kur,0000,0000,0000,,If we rush in, it'd be nearly impossible to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.35,0:26:15.65,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,He was a good man. Not that I knew him too well, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.15,0:26:19.71,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,But our only option now is to retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.67,0:26:22.89,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Kurozawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.91,0:26:25.80,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Remain on standby for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.01,0:26:28.79,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I want to stick it out a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.79,0:26:30.30,Default,Kur,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.30,0:26:31.47,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.47,0:26:32.50,Default,Kur,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.24,0:27:15.37,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,We've managed to evacuate 80 percent of the citizens so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.37,0:27:22.45,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Worst case, we can escort the remaining 20 percent into the castle in under four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.40,0:27:28.37,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Is there even any point to defending our sovereignty now? {lit; polity}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.15,0:27:32.00,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Even General True died because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:36.25,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty, please do not give up hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.25,0:27:42.21,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,The Krisnan people fought hard to regain their independence 80 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.21,0:27:47.14,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,That sense of pride will not waver, even if we surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.14,0:27:52.49,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it will fade under Athenian rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.49,0:27:56.06,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,No. There would soon be another conflict. And that is why we must fight! {timing check}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.51,0:27:59.48,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.06,0:28:01.53,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,An urgent message from our scouts!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.53,0:28:02.35,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.35,0:28:03.41,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.80,0:28:06.78,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They've broken through our advance camps.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.40,0:28:15.08,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,A massive Athenian army broke through our borders, and are headed our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.40,0:28:18.51,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Speed up the citizen's evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.51,0:28:20.42,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,One more thing, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.42,0:28:21.81,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Now what!?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.81,0:28:26.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy Knight 1st Class Rygart has headed into enemy territory to rescue his brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.05,0:28:30.89,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,and the Millennium Squadron is \Nproceeding to recover the Delphine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.25,0:28:34.81,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,What is Rygart's... no, the \NMillennium Squadron's situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.40,0:28:36.79,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.49,0:28:43.15,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the guards placed with Rygart's brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.34,0:28:47.00,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I had specifically arranged for protection. {wording?}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.18,0:28:49.72,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very sorry, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.98,0:28:59.92,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.92,0:29:02.99,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Send a message to all our remaining forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.99,0:29:05.26,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw to the capital immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.00,0:29:08.68,Default,Adv,0000,0000,0000,,Are we to abandon our first line of defense?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.39,0:29:10.79,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I authorize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.62,0:29:31.88,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.06,0:29:35.41,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We're coming with you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.41,0:29:37.33,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not recruiting men for a suicide mission.{in the manga, he resigns and goes to save rygart}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.78,0:29:41.26,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but we heard you resigned as general, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.94,0:29:46.16,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,In our current situation, no forces can be spared to rescue Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.16,0:29:49.30,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,This does not concern you men.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.30,0:29:51.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. We know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.05,0:29:59.07,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,But the seven of us have been authorized by the Vice General to act independently. {is vice general a rank?}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.07,0:30:01.65,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we may do as we please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.66,0:30:05.39,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go, General!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.02,0:30:09.53,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Let's save Rygart and return to the capital, General!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.60,0:30:14.85,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I made it clear I am no longer your general.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.85,0:30:16.33,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We're aware of that, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:20.79,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, we can't acknowledge your order to not accompany you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.18,0:30:24.63,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.36,0:30:34.90,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.55,0:30:40.55,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The pilot's regained consciousness!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.55,0:30:41.36,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Pin him down!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.35,0:30:44.19,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,They're restraining me!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.16,0:30:52.64,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin, open fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.64,0:30:53.91,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.09,0:30:58.76,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,No good!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.76,0:31:00.66,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter! Keep shooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.66,0:31:03.17,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy attack! Take cover! {lit; abort capture}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.23,0:31:06.76,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Look at me, Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.30,0:31:18.85,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.06,0:31:28.49,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Regarz...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.40,0:31:30.98,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.02,0:31:33.71,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Narvi!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.71,0:31:34.70,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Shove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.70,0:31:36.08,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.19,0:31:44.87,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The next time you ignore my orders will be your last, got it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.24,0:31:49.21,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.06,0:31:53.15,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,So all you did was drag your \Ncomrades into your own mess? {thrown under the bus, so to speak}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:31:55.33,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. They're right behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:55.89,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:31:59.62,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.62,0:32:00.53,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Take cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.12,0:32:02.44,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Did they catch up already!?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.30,0:32:08.59,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's too soon. Must be another squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.82,0:32:14.70,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe, what the hell are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.20,0:32:16.98,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Don't expose yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.83,0:32:18.79,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.74,0:32:27.57,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,You're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.40,0:32:29.97,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Nile, get behind her!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.97,0:32:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Narvi!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.79,0:32:44.65,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,You little shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.99,0:32:52.09,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even try it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.28,0:32:57.44,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.45,0:33:13.09,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,He cut through the heavy armor!? {lit; reinforced}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.09,0:33:15.09,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,That's no ordinary sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.87,0:33:17.85,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem, Girghe!?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.30,0:33:20.75,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back! I'm worried about the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.75,0:33:23.69,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Worried? Now there's a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.81,0:33:30.02,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Not something I'd expect from a guy who just ran off on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.43,0:33:34.57,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you got us into this mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.57,0:33:38.40,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we need to go back right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:39.45,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.76,0:33:42.37,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't even find your brother. {見つける =save/rescue?}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.46,0:33:44.79,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.62,0:33:54.07,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard all about you. {they've never really had a proper convo, so i think this sounds okay}{lit; rumors of you have reached my ears}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.58,0:33:57.47,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.23,0:34:03.86,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you. You even sacrificed the comrades who came to your aid. {lit; let die}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.97,0:34:10.65,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are fellow traitors. {teamkillers}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.13,0:34:14.57,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Here's some advice from your senior traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.50,0:34:18.45,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.22,0:34:21.40,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,The dead are nothing but pathetic weaklings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.86,0:34:24.90,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,These weakling's very existence is evil; a sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.90,0:34:29.46,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,They survive only by dragging down people like us. {alt; riding coattails}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.33,0:34:34.49,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,So don't worry too much
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.49,0:34:36.17,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,even if you caused their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.60,0:34:45.35,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the others lose their lives here, it's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.94,0:34:47.86,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,They're just buffoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.45,0:35:06.62,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.27,0:35:21.62,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Goodnight! {lit; die}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.35,0:35:54.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell's piloting that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.45,0:36:01.38,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Your elbow joint didn't break. Did you reinforce the frame?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.38,0:36:04.26,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, I'm grateful to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.66,0:36:25.31,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get carried away!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.89,0:36:53.81,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,If he had penetrated any further, I'd be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.04,0:37:04.32,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,You had no issues throwing aside your rifle, yet you still cling to your spear?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.83,0:37:09.24,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.48,0:37:17.17,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,You were a formidable adversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:23.03,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how it ends, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.73,0:37:25.95,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me the pain and get it over with quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.15,0:37:27.95,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.18,0:37:36.19,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,We're more alike than I had thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.70,0:37:40.61,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad said the same thing... {Baldr/Girghe's dad. can people figure it out?}{don't think so}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.02,0:37:43.05,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Really now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.05,0:37:47.71,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You act so high and mighty, and \Nyou're spouting crap like that all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.71,0:37:50.49,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You make me sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.49,0:37:51.12,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.78,0:37:53.04,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.04,0:37:54.96,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But you're just a little shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.40,0:37:58.19,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.19,0:38:01.53,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,There! That's exactly what I'm talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.53,0:38:06.69,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike me, you're a genius who can accomplish anything, but all you do is fuck around!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.69,0:38:10.36,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,While everyone else is fighting for their lives, you just sit and watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.36,0:38:12.50,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't have said it better myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.50,0:38:15.29,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me, Rygart. What are {\i1}you{\i0}  doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.98,0:38:20.21,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,What do you fight for?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.21,0:38:25.60,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me the crap about defending your homeland. What is it you really want?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.05,0:38:28.40,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What do I want?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.66,0:38:33.24,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The real reason that you've tried to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.24,0:38:36.21,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really think nobody noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.72,0:38:37.87,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.85,0:38:43.55,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,If you come back unharmed... I'll stop being angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.46,0:38:50.55,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,It's the talk of the castle. The way our dear Queen looks at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.20,0:38:53.48,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.69,0:38:59.38,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,That beautiful head doesn't turn for just any man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.38,0:39:01.89,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Not that it's any of my business, mind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.39,0:39:07.24,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I know! How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.24,0:39:12.46,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,If you can beat me, I'll grant your wish. Your one true desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.19,0:39:18.64,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I'll storm the castle, grab the Queen, and place her in your arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.50,0:39:23.80,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that just sound wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.72,0:39:32.67,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it. I'm here to protect the royal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.67,0:39:34.51,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who would attack them is my enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.34,0:39:40.85,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's settle the score right now, once and for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.85,0:39:43.77,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'm happy to oblige.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.01,0:39:53.61,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Kneeling before your enemy? A classic counterattack stance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.03,0:39:57.62,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Either that or a bold move by one man up against a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.32,0:40:01.72,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,No matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.96,0:40:05.38,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I'll crush you like a bug, Golem and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.65,0:40:13.34,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,His footwork is unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.34,0:40:14.60,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,If I tried to get up, I'd be dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.03,0:40:16.10,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there! {talking to golem}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.19,0:40:21.14,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just until Girghe extends his upper body!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.54,0:40:39.24,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.16,0:40:44.35,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Your old man told me not to mourn the dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.27,0:40:51.13,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't mean it in quite the same way, but it still makes me furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.68,0:40:55.69,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd grant my wish if I won, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.64,0:40:58.35,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Then if I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.18,0:41:02.63,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Become a general!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.62,0:41:06.39,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Surpass your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.74,0:41:14.75,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,There he is! Capture him!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.75,0:41:15.66,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.95,0:41:19.62,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.70,0:41:22.88,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,We gotta go! We can't stay here! {reverse?}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.51,0:41:36.43,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, the aim's a little off...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.91,0:41:47.81,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to kill me? Well, too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.57,0:41:56.95,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,I'll crush you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.82,0:42:00.41,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.10,0:42:03.67,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, Nike!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.67,0:42:05.35,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,That Artemis is bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.35,0:42:06.71,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,I'll snap you in two!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.79,0:42:25.06,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I see now... Those are no ordinary ligaments!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.01,0:42:36.14,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.33,0:42:46.12,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Delphine! Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.24,0:42:51.17,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Further resistance is useless! Give yourselves up!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.82,0:43:20.86,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,YOU!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.23,0:43:28.90,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Run for it, Girghe!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.17,0:43:39.63,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insane!? I said get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.09,0:43:42.80,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe!
